Q: Search in rotated sprted array-II
Question Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/search-in-rotated-sorted-array-ii/

Question Explanation: Given an rotated sorted array in that you need search for value x. And in the given array, it may contains duplicate elements.

Approach: The approach is same as the search in rotated sorted array, just like first you need to figure which part is sorted 
and then you need to find whether the value will be present sorted part or not. But it fails for the cases:-

when arr[low] = arr[mid] == arr[high]. Ex:[1,1,0,1,1,1,1]. So at this moment you need to trim the search space like low=low+1 and high=high-1 and then continue.

T.C: Best case: O(logN) and worst case: O(N)
S.C: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
    public boolean search(int[] arr, int x) {
        int n = arr.length;
        int low = 0;
        int high = n-1;
        int mid = low+(high-low)/2;
        while(high >= low){
            if(arr[mid]==x) return true;
            if(arr[mid]==arr[low] && arr[mid]==arr[high]) {
                low++;
                high--;
                continue;
            }
            if(arr[mid] >= arr[low]){
                if(x >= arr[low] && x < arr[mid]) high = mid-1;
                else low = mid+1;
            }
            else {
                if(x > arr[mid] && x <= arr[high]){
                    low = mid+1;
                }
                else high = mid-1;
            }
             mid = low+(high-low)/2;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
